  "description": [
    "CIO Parley Backs World Labor Meet 4 N The CIO NEWS November 8 1943 PHILADELPHIA Nov 6World labor unity urged by the CIO since 1941 became a major Issue of the Gtli convention here with a resolution calling for a United Nations trade union conference and with CIO acceptance of the meeting scheduled in London in June Speaking on the resolution Murray said that the London meeting was the fruit of CIO demands for full United Nations 1 labor unity and that CIO could take full credit for accomplishing It over strong opposition The President of your organi zation together with his asso ciates has been fighting des perately for the past 12 months to get a conference of this de scription convened somewhere under proper auspices and I dont think that I can overesn phasie the tremendous victory that has attended the efforts of the CIO in winning this labor conference scheduled for Lon don he said While the convention was In session the British Trades Union Congress headed by Sir Walter Citrine issued the call for the Lon don meeting According to Allied Labor News the TUC proposed 10 delegates for CIO 14 for AFL 13 for the"
